es one hand while BSL uses two hands.  This signifies that sign languages do not represent spoken languages and is highly influenced by the geographical locations and lines it develops. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Reference%0a%3c https://www.startasl.com/japanese-sign-language-jsl/#:~:text=Japanese%2520Sign%2520Language%2520(JSL)%2520is,not%2520mouthing%2520to%2520this%2520extent.%0a%3c https://www.k-international.com/blog/different-types-of-sign-language-around-the-world/%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: D:)%0a%3c (:Category: Varia:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
